      <p id="Par47">FunCoup has detected several interactors for the associated loci (Additional file <xref rid="MOESM2" ref-type="media">2</xref>: Table S2). Gene network for these genes was constructed including 16 query genes, 30 subnetwork genes and creating 124 links (Table <xref rid="Tab4" ref-type="table">4</xref>). Enrichment analysis of KEGG pathways has revealed association for cell cycle (q-value = 2.41 × 10<sup>− 20</sup>), oocyte meiosis (q-value = 1.08 × 10<sup>− 13</sup>) and progesterone-mediated oocyte maturation (q-value = 1.4 × 10<sup>− 13</sup>) among others (Fig. <xref rid="Fig3" ref-type="fig">3</xref>) (Additional file <xref rid="MOESM3" ref-type="media">3</xref>: Table S3). Top associated molecular GO terms were tranferase activity, enzyme and ribonucleotide binding (Additional file <xref rid="MOESM3" ref-type="media">3</xref>: Table S3).
